{"title_page": "Eugenio Pucciarelli", "text_new": "'''Eugenio Pucciarelli''' (August 28, 1907 &ndash; January 3, 1995) was an Argentine writer. He got a doctorate in philosophy in 1937, and worked as a teacher at the universities of Tucum\u00e1n, La Plata and Buenos Aires. He was declared professor Emeritus of the UBA. He was the president of the National Academy of Sciences of Buenos Aires.<ref>[http://www.ensayistas.org/critica/generales/C-H/argentina/pucciarelli.htm \"Eugenio Pucciarelli ante la condici\u00f3n humana\"] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pucciarelli, Eugenio}}\n[[Category:Argentine male writers]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:People from La Plata]]\n[[Category:1907 births]]\n[[Category:1995 deaths]]\n\n\n{{Argentina-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Eugenio Pucciarelli''' (August 28, 1907 &ndash; January 3, 1995) was an Argentine writer. He got a doctorate in philosophy in 1937, and worked as a teacher at the universities of Tucum\u00e1n, La Plata and Buenos Aires. He was declared professor Emeritus of the UBA. He was the president of the National Academy of Sciences of Buenos Aires.<ref>[http://www.ensayistas.org/critica/generales/C-H/argentina/pucciarelli.htm \"Eugenio Pucciarelli ante la condici\u00f3n humana\"] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pucciarelli, Eugenio}}\n[[Category:Argentine male writers]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:People from La Plata]]\n[[Category:1907 births]]\n[[Category:1995 deaths]]\n\n\n{{Argentina-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugenio_Pucciarelli"}
